    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <head>348. Telegram 1143 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d348fn1">Source:
                        Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–755. Secret; Priority; Limit
                        Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>;
                        cleared by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName> and
                        Sebald.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1955-11-07">November 7, 1955, 6:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d348-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d348-1"/>
                <p>1143. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                <p>Daily Worker story referred to our 1142 is Communists’ most flagrant violation to
                    date of agreement that substance of talks will not be revealed without prior
                    agreement or notification. Obvious purpose is to take initiative this subject
                    away from US. You should promptly deliver strong written protest to <persName
                        corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName>. You may wish mention numerous earlier
                    violations agreement by leaks to NCNA correspondent which we refrained from
                    protesting in interest progress talks, but this last leak too glaring to
                    overlook. Matter should be taken up with <persName corresp="#p_WP_1"
                        >Wang</persName> at November 10 meeting, but protest should be delivered
                    soonest to show <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> how seriously we
                    regard his breach and forestall if possible further Communist efforts publicly
                    exploit this subject prior next meeting.</p>
                <p>Department neither confirming nor denying <persName corresp="#p_WP_1"
                        >Wang</persName> has proposed joint declaration renouncing use of force.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Secretary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HH_1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
